refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public arrayReflectionEnum::getCases
An Enum may contain zero or more cases. This method retrieves all defined cases, in lexical order (that is, the order they appear in the source code).

  &reftitle.examples;



    ReflectionEnum::getCases example


<?php
enum Suit
{
    case Hearts;
    case Diamonds;
    case Clubs;
    case Spades;
}

$rEnum = new ReflectionEnum(Suit::class);

$cases = $rEnum->getCases();

foreach ($cases as $rCase) {
    var_dump($rCase->getValue());
}
?>


    &example.outputs;


enum(Suit::Hearts)
enum(Suit::Diamonds)
enum(Suit::Clubs)
enum(Suit::Spades)
